    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-01-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-02-17T16:36:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Contracting and Tax Accountability Act of 2009 - Prohibits any person who has a seriously delinquent tax debt from obtaining a federal government contract or grant. Requires federal agency heads to require prospective recipients of a contract or grant in excess of an amount equal to the simplified acquisition threshold to: (1) certify that they do not have such a debt; and (2) authorize the Secretary of the Treasury to disclose information describing whether they have such a debt. </p><p>Defines &quot;seriously delinquent tax debt&quot; and an outstanding tax debt for which a notice of lien has been filed in public records.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
